commit af9bc9e88be17693d5841876e8f2f69a279c7ff7
Author: James Y Knight <foom@fuhm.net>
Date:   Tue Apr 2 15:56:48 2024 -0400

    Address compilation failure with Clang -std=c++20. (#56)

    In C++20, vector became constexpr. Somehow, this causes the calls to
    `sub_nodes.emplace_back` to trigger an error from the attempt to
    convert `unique_ptr<MatmulNode>` (and others) to `unique_ptr<INode>`,
    when `MatmulNode` is an incomplete type.

    It seems like that _should_ have been an error before as well, since
    that conversion is only valid if `MatmulNode` is known to be a subtype
    of INode. But, I suppose previously it was deferred until after
    `matmul.h` had been included, and now due to constexpr the conversion
    attempt is triggered eagerly.

    To resolve, put the definitions of the functions in the headers
    associated with each type.

    Co-authored-by: Anerudhan Gopal <agopal@nvidia.com>
